-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-29/hungary-s-producer-prices-decline-for-third-month-in-august.html
Hungarian producer prices, an early
indicator of inflation trends, dropped for a third consecutive
month in August.  Factory-gate prices fell 0.1 percent from a year earlier,
the Budapest-based  statistics office  said today in an e-mail.
The median estimate of five economists surveyed by Bloomberg was
for a 0.2 percent rise. Prices rose 0.7 percent in the month.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Edith Balazs in Budapest at 
